1
00:00:02,999 --> 00:00:04,334
Here's another one.

2
00:00:04,334 --> 00:00:05,868
If you were really pro-life,

3
00:00:05,868 --> 00:00:08,004
you'd pay for the upkeep of the child

4
00:00:08,004 --> 00:00:10,440
until he or she reaches 18.

5
00:00:10,440 --> 00:00:12,075
If you're not prepared to do that,

6
00:00:12,075 --> 00:00:14,644
then you have no
right to oppose abortion.

7
00:00:14,644 --> 00:00:15,645
- There are several reasons

8
00:00:15,645 --> 00:00:17,680
why this argument doesn't work.

9
00:00:17,680 --> 00:00:20,850
If you see a child
being abused by their parents,

10
00:00:20,850 --> 00:00:22,552
do you call the authorities only

11
00:00:22,552 --> 00:00:25,788
if you're prepared to
raise him or her to adulthood?

12
00:00:25,788 --> 00:00:28,791
Just because we can't
adopt every unwanted child

13
00:00:28,791 --> 00:00:31,394
doesn't mean we
shouldn't try to save their lives.

14
00:00:31,394 --> 00:00:34,263
- But suppose pro-lifers
really don't care about babies

15
00:00:34,263 --> 00:00:35,298
after they're born.

16
00:00:35,298 --> 00:00:37,734
Does that mean it's
okay to let them be slaughtered?

17
00:00:37,734 --> 00:00:38,901
- No, no.

18
00:00:38,901 --> 00:00:42,005
- It's also rather
melodramatic and manipulative

19
00:00:42,005 --> 00:00:44,407
to say that anyone
who doesn't actively support

20
00:00:44,407 --> 00:00:48,644
a child's welfare after
birth must want that child dead.

21
00:00:48,644 --> 00:00:51,314
If someone comes to
your door asking for donations

22
00:00:51,314 --> 00:00:53,750
for cancer research and you decline,

23
00:00:53,750 --> 00:00:56,719
does that mean you want
everyone with cancer to die?

24
00:00:56,719 --> 00:00:57,420
Of course not.

25
00:00:57,420 --> 00:00:57,987
- No.

26
00:00:57,987 --> 00:01:01,257
And the idea that
pro-lifers are pro-birth only

27
00:01:01,257 --> 00:01:02,291
is not even true.

28
00:01:02,291 --> 00:01:02,992
- That's right.

29
00:01:02,992 --> 00:01:04,861
- Pro-lifers are at the forefront

30
00:01:04,861 --> 00:01:07,397
of care for mothers and babies.

31
00:01:07,397 --> 00:01:10,333
In the US, pro-life
pregnancy counseling centers

32
00:01:10,333 --> 00:01:12,802
outnumber Planned
Parenthood abortion meals

33
00:01:12,802 --> 00:01:14,203
over three to one.

34
00:01:14,203 --> 00:01:17,140
Yet those centers receive
little to no government funding

35
00:01:17,140 --> 00:01:21,110
while Planned Parenthood
receives $500 million a year.

36
00:01:21,110 --> 00:01:23,513
- A pro-abortion
group called Action Canada

37
00:01:23,513 --> 00:01:25,982
for Sexual Health
and Rights has complained

38
00:01:25,982 --> 00:01:29,585
that in Canada, there
are more crisis pregnancy centers

39
00:01:29,585 --> 00:01:32,021
than abortion
providers, including hospitals.

40
00:01:32,021 --> 00:01:32,989
- Sounds great.

41
00:01:32,989 --> 00:01:35,491
This group has claimed
that crisis pregnancy centers

42
00:01:35,491 --> 00:01:37,460
are giving out false information,

43
00:01:37,460 --> 00:01:39,796
but they haven't offered any real proof.

44
00:01:39,796 --> 00:01:42,699
One objection they have
is that some of these centers

45
00:01:42,699 --> 00:01:46,102
offer ultrasounds,
which they say can trick people

46
00:01:46,102 --> 00:01:48,805
into believing
they're a medical facility.

47
00:01:48,805 --> 00:01:50,840
- The gas station has an ATM,

48
00:01:50,840 --> 00:01:53,276
but no one mistakes it for a bang.

49
00:01:53,276 --> 00:01:55,711
But an ultrasound
could help a woman realize

50
00:01:55,711 --> 00:01:57,780
her baby is not just a clump of cells.

51
00:01:57,780 --> 00:01:58,748
- That's right.

52
00:01:58,748 --> 00:02:00,316
- That's a factor of decision.

53
00:02:00,316 --> 00:02:01,884
Maybe that's the real objection.

54
00:02:01,884 --> 00:02:04,287
- Yeah, one research paper indicated

55
00:02:04,287 --> 00:02:06,989
that pregnant women who
visit crisis pregnancy centers

56
00:02:06,989 --> 00:02:10,927
are 20% less likely to
choose abortion than those who don't.

57
00:02:10,927 --> 00:02:11,561
- Good.

58
00:02:11,561 --> 00:02:14,397
- The study authors
suggested that this must be

59
00:02:14,397 --> 00:02:17,700
at least partly
because the centers lie to people.

60
00:02:17,700 --> 00:02:20,536
For example, NARAL Pro-Choice America

61
00:02:20,536 --> 00:02:24,140
conducted an undercover
investigation in which they said,

62
00:02:24,140 --> 00:02:27,744
"More than 67% of
the locations intentionally

63
00:02:27,744 --> 00:02:31,881
referred to the fetus as
baby and told our investigator

64
00:02:31,881 --> 00:02:35,284
she was already a mother
because she was already pregnant."

65
00:02:35,284 --> 00:02:37,019
That's certainly a pro-life perspective,

66
00:02:37,019 --> 00:02:39,522
but it's also factually accurate.

67
00:02:39,522 --> 00:02:41,424
- Most pregnancy centers are upfront

68
00:02:41,424 --> 00:02:44,393
about what services
they do and do not provide.

69
00:02:44,393 --> 00:02:46,329
The name alone, pregnancy centers,

70
00:02:46,329 --> 00:02:48,865
should be a clue that
their focus is on pregnancy,

71
00:02:48,865 --> 00:02:49,532
non-abortion.

72
00:02:49,532 --> 00:02:50,266
- That's right.

73
00:02:50,266 --> 00:02:52,769
- Oddly enough, many
offer counseling for those

74
00:02:52,769 --> 00:02:54,203
who do choose an abortion,

75
00:02:54,203 --> 00:02:56,405
even though they don't perform them.

76
00:02:56,405 --> 00:02:59,242
- Meanwhile, it's been
suggested that other organizations

77
00:02:59,242 --> 00:03:01,177
tend to give the impression that abortion

78
00:03:01,177 --> 00:03:02,545
is the only option.

79
00:03:02,545 --> 00:03:03,312
It's not.

80
00:03:03,312 --> 00:03:06,349
- No, adoption is a
great alternative for any mother

81
00:03:06,349 --> 00:03:09,185
who feels unprepared to raise a child,

82
00:03:09,185 --> 00:03:11,554
but wants the child to live a happy life.

83
00:03:11,554 --> 00:03:13,523
There are more couples wanting to adopt

84
00:03:13,523 --> 00:03:15,725
than there are babies available.

